{
  "local_port": 57160,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do I get snapchat notifications of some people but not others?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why you might receive Snapchat notifications for some people but not others. Here are the most common explanations:\n\n### 1. **Notification Settings for Individual Users**\n   - Snapchat allows you to customize notifications for specific friends. If you\u2019ve enabled notifications for one person but not another, you\u2019ll only receive alerts for the ones you\u2019ve allowed.\n   - To check: Go to your **Friend List**, tap the gear icon next to a friend\u2019s name, and ensure \"**Allow Notifications**\" is turned on.\n\n### 2. **App Notification Settings**\n   - If Snapchat notifications are turned off at the app level in your phone's settings, you won\u2019t receive any notifications. Alternatively, notifications might be enabled for the app but restricted for certain types (e.g., snaps, messages, or story updates).\n   - To check: Go to your phone's **Settings** > **Apps** > **Snapchat** > **Notifications**, and ensure they\u2019re enabled.\n\n### 3. **Do Not Disturb or Muted Conversations**\n   - If you\u2019ve muted a specific conversation or turned on **Do Not Disturb** for a friend, you won\u2019t receive notifications from them.\n   - To check: Open the chat with the person in question, tap the menu (three vertical dots), and see if **Do Not Disturb** is enabled.\n\n### 4. **Snapchat Notification Preferences**\n   - Within the Snapchat app, you can adjust your notification preferences for different types of alerts (e.g., snaps, chats, stories, etc.). If certain types of notifications are turned off, you won\u2019t receive them.\n   - To check: Go to your **Profile** > **Settings** > **Notifications** and adjust your preferences.\n\n### 5. **Friend Activity**\n   - If someone hasn\u2019t sent you a snap, message, or added to their story recently, you won\u2019t receive notifications from them. Notifications are triggered by activity.\n\n### 6. **App Glitches or Updates**\n   - Sometimes, glitches or bugs in the app can cause uneven notifications. Ensure your Snapchat app is updated to the latest version. If the issue persists, try reinstalling the app.\n\n### 7. **Device-Specific Settings**\n   - Your phone\u2019s battery-saving mode or app optimization settings might restrict Snapchat notifications. Check if Snapchat is being limited by these settings.\n\n### 8. **Blocked or Removed Friends**\n   - If you\u2019ve blocked or removed someone as a friend, you won\u2019t receive notifications from them.\n\nBy checking these settings and preferences, you should be able to figure out why you\u2019re receiving notifications from some people but not others. Let me know if you need further help!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
